From: Danny Kukawka <danny.kukawka@bisect.de>
Date: Fri, 24 Feb 2012 03:45:56 +0000
Subject: ixgbevf: print MAC via printk format specifier
Patch-mainline: v3.4-rc1
Git-commit: f794e7efe40147ed0c34f889b75298fec10e66b8
References: bnc#795301 FATE#313663

Print MAC/dev_addr via printk extended format specifier %pM
instead of custom code.

Signed-off-by: Danny Kukawka <danny.kukawka@bisect.de>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/ixgbevf_main.c |    8 +-------
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 7 deletions(-)
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/ixgbevf_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/ixgbevf_main.c
@@ -3455,13 +3455,7 @@ static int __devinit ixgbevf_probe(struc
 	ixgbevf_init_last_counter_stats(adapter);
 
 	/* print the MAC address */
-	hw_dbg(hw, "%2.2x:%2.2x:%2.2x:%2.2x:%2.2x:%2.2x\n",
-	       netdev->dev_addr[0],
-	       netdev->dev_addr[1],
-	       netdev->dev_addr[2],
-	       netdev->dev_addr[3],
-	       netdev->dev_addr[4],
-	       netdev->dev_addr[5]);
+	hw_dbg(hw, "%pM\n", netdev->dev_addr);
 
 	hw_dbg(hw, "MAC: %d\n", hw->mac.type);
 
